==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dichromatic
<hw>Di`chro*mat"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>di-</ets> + <ets>chromatic</ets>: cf. Gr. <?/.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having or exhibiting two colors.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having two color varieties, or
two phases differing in color, independently of age or sex, as in
certain birds and insects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dichromatism</ent>⟦br⟧
